      "name": "Green Cardamom Pods",
      "amount": "1-2 pods"
    },
    {
      "name": "Sugar",
      "amount": "3 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Vanilla Extract",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Almond Milk",
      "amount": "1 cup (dairy-free)"
    },
    {
      "name": "Flax Seeds",
      "amount": "1 tablespoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Custard Powder",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Water",
      "amount": "3/4 cup"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt",
      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Roast cardamom pods for about 5-10 minutes until fragrant, then grind into a powder.",
    "In a saucepan, mix sugar and vanilla extract. Add almond milk, flax seeds, custard powder, and salt.",
    "Stir continuously over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken and boil. Reduce heat, continue cooking until thickened, about 5 minutes more.",
    "Pour into a greased tart pan or ramekins and chill for at least 2 hours before serving."
  ],
